<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3177ec76cfd6747e819fc0f285979214 sig_cn_org=23ee86f22aafc4d50e12402c038a6a38 source=16.8 
     <para>
      Fix <application>psql</application> to safely handle file path names
      that are encoded in SJIS (Tom Lane)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;998c4fc7c">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复<application>psql</application>以安全处理以SJIS编码的文件路径名
      （Tom Lane）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;998c4fc7c">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3177ec76cfd6747e819fc0f285979214 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=a31489adfc8b22c071a5235bd5a817aa sig_cn_org=f04c07af4c22b3dd9249d6cdec4ea971 source=16.8 
     <para>
      Some two-byte characters in SJIS have a second byte that is equal to
      ASCII backslash (<literal>\</literal>).  These characters were
      corrupted by path name normalization, preventing access to files
      whose names include such characters.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      SJIS中的某些双字节字符的第二个字节等于ASCII反斜杠
      (<literal>\</literal>)。这些字符在路径名规范化时被破坏，
      导致无法访问包含这些字符的文件。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=a31489adfc8b22c071a5235bd5a817aa -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
