 <sect1 id="release-16-5">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=37c6cb0c004e361f0a9bc90f9a14418a sig_cn_org=b4f35177dfffa29eea97cfa787022659 source=16.8 
  <title>Release 16.5</title>
________________________________________________________-->
  <title>版本 16.5</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=37c6cb0c004e361f0a9bc90f9a14418a -->

  <formalpara>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c45e8127eac45f2347bf1713afaeffda sig_cn_org=253305b4c6dff5b87ef36e3c2d95e52e source=15.7 
  <title>Release date:</title>
________________________________________________________-->
  <title>发布日期：</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c45e8127eac45f2347bf1713afaeffda -->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c3f5709eb4f0214271fc9dfa4c103cb3 sig_cn_org=c3f5709eb4f0214271fc9dfa4c103cb3 source=16.8 
  <para>2024-11-14</para>
________________________________________________________-->
  <para>2024-11-14</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c3f5709eb4f0214271fc9dfa4c103cb3 -->
  </formalpara>

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=7c500e370bdd323a72af1dac88079ff3 sig_cn_org=cc7d79ddefcab46c6503442d78785c37 source=16.8 
  <para>
   This release contains a variety of fixes from 16.4.
   For information about new features in major release 16, see
   <xref linkend="release-16"/>.
  </para>
________________________________________________________-->
  <para>
   此版本包含从16.4修复的各种问题。
   有关16的主要版本中新功能的信息，请参见
   <xref linkend="release-16"/>。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=7c500e370bdd323a72af1dac88079ff3 -->

  <sect2 id="release-16-5-migration">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=7a575800738e35f0bf68111064d677d7 sig_cn_org=2155e32ccfa5bcf4cf1a057cba8cfa96 source=16.8 
   <title>Migration to Version 16.5</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本16.5</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=7a575800738e35f0bf68111064d677d7 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=ab87a2b9a562c1c18cc090d4910f7109 sig_cn_org=ecf94fca947a20bacd9abb4942dbe5d7 source=16.8 
   <para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 16.X.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    对于运行16.X的用户，不需要进行转储/恢复。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=ab87a2b9a562c1c18cc090d4910f7109 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=1fb2d416f6883355a960fdfcc630e501 sig_cn_org=8f9f91cd06dfcb68d46c3f393240b0c5 source=16.8 
   <para>
    However, if you have ever detached a partition from a partitioned
    table that has a foreign-key reference to another partitioned table,
    and not dropped the former partition, then you may have catalog and/or
    data corruption to repair, as detailed in the fifth changelog entry
    below.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    然而，如果您曾经从一个分区表中分离出一个分区，并且该分区表具有对另一个
    分区表的外键引用，而没有删除前者的分区，那么您可能需要修复目录和/或数据
    损坏，具体细节请参见下面的第五个变更日志条目。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=1fb2d416f6883355a960fdfcc630e501 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=8348580e8eebc734ef50ef264480ec64 sig_cn_org=d61230ac213af9689e97a28b877c3135 source=16.8 
   <para>
    Also, if you are upgrading from a version earlier than 16.3,
    see <xref linkend="release-16-3"/>.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    此外，如果您正在从早于16.3的版本升级，
    请参阅<xref linkend="release-16-3"/>。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=8348580e8eebc734ef50ef264480ec64 -->
  </sect2>

  <sect2 id="release-16-5-changes">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=e161fef38e54e54458e215e5f978ef9b sig_cn_org=f104d50dd9d4dd802f94229ebe5bc097 source=15.7 
   <title>Changes</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>变更</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=e161fef38e54e54458e215e5f978ef9b -->

   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Nathan Bossart <nathan@postgresql.org>
Branch: master [cd7ab5753] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [edcda9bb4] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [562289460] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [6db5ea8de] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [4e51030af] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
Branch: REL_13_STABLE [952ff31e2] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
Branch: REL_12_STABLE [448525e8a] 2024-11-11 09:00:00 -0600
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=93012a47b7850e8a77022f17f885b5f2 sig_cn_org=c03aa8aba6040fa7d35aa83b28f90426 source=16.8 
     <para>
      Ensure cached plans are marked as dependent on the calling role when
      RLS applies to a non-top-level table reference (Nathan Bossart)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;562289460">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      确保在调用角色时，缓存计划被标记为依赖于调用角色，当RLS适用于非顶级
      表引用时（Nathan Bossart）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;562289460">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=93012a47b7850e8a77022f17f885b5f2 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=a64ab1b252fc7fb64f28b8f40db0aa55 sig_cn_org=af11761be56e749c3bbdf78ee5f9871c source=16.8 
     <para>
      If a CTE, subquery, sublink, security invoker view, or coercion
      projection in a query references a table with row-level security
      policies, we neglected to mark the resulting plan as potentially
      dependent on which role is executing it.  This could lead to later
      query executions in the same session using the wrong plan, and then
      returning or hiding rows that should have been hidden or returned
      instead.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      如果查询中的CTE、子查询、子链接、安全调用者视图或强制投影引用了具有行级
      安全策略的表，我们未能将生成的计划标记为可能依赖于执行它的角色。这可能导
      致同一会话中的后续查询执行使用错误的计划，从而返回或隐藏本应隐藏或返回的
      行。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=a64ab1b252fc7fb64f28b8f40db0aa55 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=ab3a30581c8ed2399e290f6f77bf8ee5 sig_cn_org=14acc0a106b7395e775c8748a879291a source=16.8 
     <para>
      The <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> Project thanks
      Wolfgang Walther for reporting this problem.
      (CVE-2024-10976)
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>项目感谢
      Wolfgang Walther 报告了此问题。
      （CVE-2024-10976）
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=ab3a30581c8ed2399e290f6f77bf8ee5 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--
Author: Michael Paquier <michael@paquier.xyz>
Branch: master [bf8835ea9] 2024-11-11 10:19:52 +0900
Branch: REL_17_STABLE [a5cc4c667] 2024-11-11 10:19:56 +0900
Branch: REL_16_STABLE [67d28bd02] 2024-11-11 10:19:58 +0900
Branch: REL_15_STABLE [d2c3e31c1] 2024-11-11 10:19:59 +0900
Branch: REL_14_STABLE [e6c945476] 2024-11-11 10:20:01 +0900
Branch: REL_13_STABLE [7b49707b7] 2024-11-11 10:20:02 +0900
Branch: REL_12_STABLE [2a951ef0a] 2024-11-11 10:20:03 +0900
-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=f913846c0327bc2b962dc3c63e0b9ad2 sig_cn_org=f958b70ae24ff8e1e7972ead56dbe6eb source=16.8 
     <para>
      Make <application>libpq</application> discard error messages
      received during SSL or GSS protocol negotiation (Jacob Champion)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;67d28bd02">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      使<application>libpq</application>丢弃在SSL或GSS协议协商期间收到的错误消息
      （Jacob Champion）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;67d28bd02">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=f913846c0327bc2b962dc3c63e0b9ad2 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=1d87204bc60e93f8049f5e9dc6ec7a2d sig_cn_org=b5e86b5bf963284b6571fc71e40a828f source=16.8 
     <para>
      An error message received before encryption negotiation is completed
      might have been injected by a man-in-the-middle, rather than being
      real server output.  Reporting it opens the door to various security
      hazards; for example, the message might spoof a query result that a
      careless user could mistake for correct output.  The best answer
      seems to be to discard such data and rely only
      on <application>libpq</application>'s own report of the connection
      failure.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      在加密协商完成之前收到的错误消息可能是由中间人攻击注入的，
      而不是真正的服务器输出。报告此类消息会带来各种安全隐患；
      例如，该消息可能伪造一个查询结果，而粗心的用户可能会误以为
      是正确的输出。最好的解决方案似乎是丢弃这些数据，并仅依赖
      <application>libpq</application>自身的连接失败报告。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=1d87204bc60e93f8049f5e9dc6ec7a2d -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=8aeca340f5b82ff06de1c45e76b91a27 sig_cn_org=1532a2518bc682abbe61ad4ce820c3c6 source=16.8 
     <para>
      The <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> Project thanks
      Jacob Champion for reporting this problem.
      (CVE-2024-10977)
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>项目感谢
      Jacob Champion 报告了此问题。
      (CVE-2024-10977)
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=8aeca340f5b82ff06de1c45e76b91a27 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
