<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=6d297ce37b7ed7d6f68cd9bd35a4037c sig_cn_org=390eeb0adb674c210ed26e07b28ff300 source=16.8 
     <para>
      Fix unintended interactions between <command>SET SESSION
      AUTHORIZATION</command> and <command>SET ROLE</command> (Tom Lane)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;ae340d031">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;95f5a5237">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复<command>SET SESSION AUTHORIZATION</command>和<command>SET ROLE</command>
      之间的意外交互 (Tom Lane)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;ae340d031">&sect;</ulink>
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;95f5a5237">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=6d297ce37b7ed7d6f68cd9bd35a4037c -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=cc6cba54d16b36a85f31cb5d0fabc4ae sig_cn_org=5d8d07d4d3584781cfb2c5bfc0e97584 source=16.8 
     <para>
      The SQL standard mandates that <command>SET SESSION
      AUTHORIZATION</command> have a side-effect of doing <command>SET
      ROLE NONE</command>.  Our implementation of that was flawed,
      creating more interaction between the two settings than intended.
      Notably, rolling back a transaction that had done <command>SET
      SESSION AUTHORIZATION</command> would revert <literal>ROLE</literal>
      to <literal>NONE</literal> even if that had not been the previous
      state, so that the effective user ID might now be different from
      what it had been before the transaction.  Transiently
      setting <varname>session_authorization</varname> in a
      function <literal>SET</literal> clause had a similar effect.
      A related bug was that if a parallel worker
      inspected <literal>current_setting('role')</literal>, it
      saw <literal>none</literal> even when it should see something else.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      SQL标准要求<command>SET SESSION AUTHORIZATION</command>具有执行
      <command>SET ROLE NONE</command>的副作用。我们的实现存在缺陷，
      导致这两个设置之间的交互比预期的更多。特别是，回滚一个执行了
      <command>SET SESSION AUTHORIZATION</command>的事务会将<literal>ROLE</literal>
      恢复为<literal>NONE</literal>，即使这并不是之前的状态，因此有效的用户ID
      可能会与事务之前的状态不同。在函数<literal>SET</literal>子句中临时设置
      <varname>session_authorization</varname>也会产生类似的效果。
      一个相关的错误是，如果一个并行工作者检查
      <literal>current_setting('role')</literal>，它会看到
      <literal>none</literal>，即使它应该看到其他内容。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=cc6cba54d16b36a85f31cb5d0fabc4ae -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=060ba57a0c776b7f504ff41032f9d937 sig_cn_org=be7325f3121123c5a9c3b6bd08528767 source=16.8 
     <para>
      The <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> Project thanks
      Tom Lane for reporting this problem.
      (CVE-2024-10978)
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>项目感谢
      Tom Lane 报告了此问题。
      (CVE-2024-10978)
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=060ba57a0c776b7f504ff41032f9d937 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
