-->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=cc813427d69a5116989f0a2ac0946488 sig_cn_org=06cfdad8d283607b25447958fcb4bb36 source=16.8 
     <para>
      Fix behavior of stable functions called from
      a <command>CALL</command> statement's argument list, when
      the <command>CALL</command> is within a
      PL/pgSQL <literal>EXCEPTION</literal> block (Tom Lane)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;25d639eea">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      修复从<command>CALL</command>语句的参数列表中调用的稳定函数的行为，
      当<command>CALL</command>位于PL/pgSQL <literal>EXCEPTION</literal>块中时
      （Tom Lane）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;25d639eea">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=cc813427d69a5116989f0a2ac0946488 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=4bc1508f43f0e4ca08ca798567855395 sig_cn_org=5f2721897893797446707d7bf9357358 source=16.8 
     <para>
      As with a similar fix in our previous quarterly releases, this case
      allowed such functions to be passed the wrong snapshot, causing them
      to see stale values of rows modified since the start of the outer
      transaction.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      与我们之前季度版本中的类似修复一样，此问题允许将错误的快照传递给
      此类函数，导致它们看到自外部事务开始以来修改的行的过时值。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=4bc1508f43f0e4ca08ca798567855395 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
