     <para>
      Avoid use of <function>pnstrdup()</function>
      in <application>ecpglib</application> (Jacob Champion)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;ee2997c67">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      避免在<application>ecpglib</application>中使用<function>pnstrdup()</function>
      (Jacob Champion)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;ee2997c67">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=434431f00ecbbcf32eefbcfb0f1af69b -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=7ed1268b33f504545a49a765a7ed66b2 sig_cn_org=314615fb40fa39c80c96033e36019235 source=16.8 
     <para>
      That function will call <function>exit()</function> on
      out-of-memory, which is undesirable in a library.  The calling code
      already handles allocation failures properly.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      该函数将在内存不足时调用<function>exit()</function>，这在库中是不理想的。
      调用代码已经正确处理了分配失败的情况。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=7ed1268b33f504545a49a765a7ed66b2 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
