<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=7b0e11dabfa05561cacb9a35ed3b54c5 sig_cn_org=401b3893b4579296aeff2efd1ec1539c source=16.8 
     <para>
      In <application>ecpglib</application>, fix out-of-bounds read when
      parsing incorrect datetime input (Bruce Momjian, Pavel Nekrasov)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;a1e613b81">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      在<application>ecpglib</application>中，修复了解析错误日期时间输入时的
      越界读取问题（Bruce Momjian, Pavel Nekrasov）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;a1e613b81">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=7b0e11dabfa05561cacb9a35ed3b54c5 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=0fd41a8b61ce1a7cafb6d89253eabc2c sig_cn_org=6711baa66a42d539f03bdca255208369 source=16.8 
     <para>
      It was possible to try to read the location just before the start of
      a constant array.  Real-world consequences seem minimal, though.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      可以尝试读取常量数组开始之前的位置。实际影响似乎很小。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=0fd41a8b61ce1a7cafb6d89253eabc2c -->
    </listitem>

