<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=957fa7b88a87420660a4761f09f34829 sig_cn_org=eb509e37977b399198d6181efd7b9292 source=16.8 
     <para>
      Prevent unauthorized code execution
      during <application>pg_dump</application> (Masahiko Sawada)
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;6aba85a4b">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      防止在<application>pg_dump</application>期间执行未经授权的代码
      （Masahiko Sawada）
      <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;6aba85a4b">&sect;</ulink>
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=957fa7b88a87420660a4761f09f34829 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=f4697a90610a6b958a1f2034f00b0c2a sig_cn_org=1f71771d4d5ecf8422046fa71e9ca1fb source=16.8 
     <para>
      An attacker able to create and drop non-temporary objects could
      inject SQL code that would be executed by a
      concurrent <application>pg_dump</application> session with the
      privileges of the role running <application>pg_dump</application>
      (which is often a superuser).  The attack involves replacing a
      sequence or similar object with a view or foreign table that will
      execute malicious code.  To prevent this, introduce a new server
      parameter <varname>restrict_nonsystem_relation_kind</varname> that
      can disable expansion of non-builtin views as well as access to
      foreign tables, and teach <application>pg_dump</application> to set
      it when available.  Note that the attack is prevented only if
      both <application>pg_dump</application> and the server it is dumping
      from are new enough to have this fix.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      能够创建和删除非临时对象的攻击者可能会注入SQL代码，这些代码将由
      并发的<application>pg_dump</application>会话以运行
      <application>pg_dump</application>的角色权限执行（通常是超级用户）。
      该攻击涉及用一个视图或外部表替换序列或类似对象，从而执行恶意代码。
      为了防止这种情况，引入了一个新的服务器参数
      <varname>restrict_nonsystem_relation_kind</varname>，它可以禁用非内置视图的扩展
      以及对外部表的访问，并教会<application>pg_dump</application>在可用时设置它。
      请注意，只有当<application>pg_dump</application>和它正在转储的服务器
      都足够新以包含此修复时，才能防止该攻击。
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=f4697a90610a6b958a1f2034f00b0c2a -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=1e6fe60901eaf5feb8ba53b9076f4268 sig_cn_org=ac331042a00fc4c4328d32a636ac1bf2 source=16.8 
     <para>
      The <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> Project thanks
      Noah Misch for reporting this problem.
      (CVE-2024-7348)
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      <productname>PostgreSQL</productname>项目感谢
      Noah Misch 报告了此问题。
      (CVE-2024-7348)
</para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=1e6fe60901eaf5feb8ba53b9076f4268 -->
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
