Author: Tom Lane <tgl@sss.pgh.pa.us>
2022-09-27 [385366426] Introduce GUC_NO_RESET flag.
-->

      <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=588a3c9605731b941ea034b791a1ce11 sig_cn_org=da5a5fb694fbc2ab252bc44968a36793 source=16.8 
       <para>
        Tighten restrictions on which server variables can be reset
        (Masahiko Sawada)
        <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;385366426">&sect;</ulink>
       </para>
________________________________________________________-->
       <para>
        收紧对可以重置的服务器变量的限制
        （Masahiko Sawada）
        <ulink url="&commit_baseurl;385366426">&sect;</ulink>
       </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=588a3c9605731b941ea034b791a1ce11 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=a2621e433075c368f706ec8cf86bb29e sig_cn_org=db3b2d563f399a2be76a923b7bf43bb4 source=16.8 
       <para>
        Previously, while certain variables, like <link
        linkend="guc-default-transaction-isolation"><varname>transaction_isolation</varname></link>,
        were not affected by <link linkend="sql-reset"><command>RESET
        ALL</command></link>, they could be individually reset in
        inappropriate situations.
       </para>
________________________________________________________-->
       <para>
        以前，某些变量，例如<link
        linkend="guc-default-transaction-isolation"><varname>transaction_isolation</varname></link>，
        不会受到<link linkend="sql-reset"><command>RESET
        ALL</command></link>的影响，但它们可能在不适当的情况下被单独重置。
       </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=a2621e433075c368f706ec8cf86bb29e -->
      </listitem>

